<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648176>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 11: Map of the distribution of Buthus species in Algeria, Tunisia, Libya, and Egypt. Light green area, B. paris; blue area, B. tunetanus; yellow rhombus, B. chambiensis; overturned orange triangle, B. dunlopi; pale blue oval, B. tassili; violet star, B. pusillus; pink triangle, B. barcaeus; dark green hexagon, B. egyptiensis; brown square, B. adrianae; purple pentagon, B. orientalis; black circle, B. israelis; red cross, B. lourencoi sp. n.; question mark, possible locality of B. intumescens." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4648176/files/figure.png" .

